With the ability to comfortably accommodate around 200 guests, it is a spacious and adaptable space that ensures ample room for large gatherings and celebrations. What truly sets this room apart is its breathtaking view of the Intracoastal Waterway and the scenic Birch State Park. This picturesque backdrop elevates the ambiance of any event, offering guests a stunning visual experience that adds a touch of natural beauty to their celebration. One of the standout features of the Intracoastal Room is its covered Veranda, which can accommodate up to 125 guests. This outdoor extension provides a unique opportunity for guests to enjoy the beauty of the surroundings while being sheltered from the elements. The covered patio offers an impressive outdoor setting that seamlessly blends with the indoor space, allowing for an effortless transition between the two areas. This flexibility grants event planners and hosts the creative freedom to design and tailor their events to their specific vision, creating a truly unforgettable atmosphere for attendees. Back to Top Commodore's Lounge Whether it's a business luncheon, a cocktail party, a bridal shower, or a small conference, the Commodore's Lounge offers a versatile canvas that can be customized to match a range of event themes and styles. The Commodore's Lounge boasts a captivating view of the courtyard, adding to its overall charm. With the ability to comfortable host approximately 60 people, it offers an intimate ambiance that is well-suited for a variety of events. Back to Top Main Dining Room The Main Dining Room is an exceptional venue known for its versatility and charm, making it the ideal choice for a wide range of celebrations and gatherings. With the ability to comfortably host up to 200 guests, it stands as a spacious and accommodating setting that can cater to both intimate gatherings and larger events. Its prime location on the first floor of the Clubhouse further adds to its allure, as it ensures easy accessibility for all attendees, including those with mobility considerations. Back to Top Auxiliary Patio The Auxiliary Patio is a truly captivating space that promises a remarkable outdoor experience. Its panoramic vistas include the Club’s Olympic-size pool, the Marina, and the serenity of the Intracoastal Waterway, creating a breathtaking backdrop that sets the stage for memorable gatherings. With the capacity to comfortably accommodate approximately 40 guests under cover, this space is tailor-made for intimate outdoor events that capture the beauty of nature. Whether it's a romantic wedding ceremony, a cozy birthday celebration, a small corporate retreat, or a family reunion, the Auxiliary Patio ensures that every attendee feels connected to the environment and to one another. Back to Top Boardroom The Boardroom is designed to provide a comfortable and productive environment for meetings and discussions. Equipped with advanced audio and visual technology, the Boardroom is optimized for seamless communication and presentations. The built-in refreshment station adds an element of convenience and consideration for participants. Providing refreshments and light bites within the room minimizes disruptions, allowing meetings to proceed smoothly without the need for attendees to leave the space. Whether it's a formal business presentation, a strategic planning session, or any other type of professional gathering, the amenities cater to the needs of participants and contribute to a productive and comfortable meeting experience. Back to Top Courtyard With native plants and lush green grass surrounding meandering pathways, the Courtyard provides a picturesque setting for any event. Offering a unique blend of natural elements and striking architecture, it creates an inviting and memorable atmosphere. Back to Top Weather 81 °F scattered clouds

This Club is not only open to its members but also extends a warm welcome to guests from The Florida Council of Yacht Clubs, as well as other yacht clubs both national and internationally. The Club offers dock space for its members who wish to stop by lunch or dinner, providing a convenient and enjoyable way to experience the waterfront atmosphere. CRYC holds a special place for boaters who appreciate the Club’s location right in the heart of Fort Lauderdale, making it a hidden gem for those who love maritime activities and beautiful surroundings. Weather 81 °F scattered clouds
